Scenario: the list command emits one line per BC declared in the manifest
  Given the manifest file contains entries for six BCs
  When I run the sync command's list operation
  Then the output contains exactly six lines
  And each line contains the canonical name of one declared BC

Scenario: the list command output is machine-parseable
  Given the manifest file contains entries for six BCs
  When I run the sync command's list operation
  Then a script can extract all six canonical BC names from stdout
  using only standard text processing tools (no LLM, no custom parser)

Scenario: the list command exits zero when the manifest is valid
  Given the manifest file is syntactically valid and contains at least one BC entry
  When I run the sync command's list operation
  Then the command exits zero
